(k) Any other day designated as a legal holiday by the President, the Congress,r the Mayor or the Council of the District of Columbia, on the actual day theegal holiday is celebrated by the government of the District of Columbia.
Office of Investigations and Enforcement &#8211; the investigative divisionithin the Department of Consumer and Regulatory Affairs. Party &#8211; a respondent, the Corporation Counsel, the Director, or any othererson recognized as a party in a particular proceeding. Person &#8211; an individual, corporation, business trust, estate, trust,artnership, limited liability company, association, joint venture, government,overnmental subdivision, agency, or instrumentality, public corporation, or anyther legal or commercial entity. Professional-sports-services contract &#8211; an agreement under which anndividual is employed, or agrees to render services, as a player on arofessional sports team, with a professional sports organization, or as arofessional athlete. Record &#8211; information that is inscribed on a tangible medium or that istored in an electronic or other medium and is retrievable in perceivable form. Registrant &#8211; a person registered under this chapter. Registration &#8211; registration as an athlete agent pursuant to this chapter. Respondent &#8211; a person against whom an adverse action is contemplated,roposed, or taken. State &#8211; a State of the United States, the District of Columbia, Puertoico, the United States Virgin Islands, or any territory or insular possessionubject to the jurisdiction of the United States. Student-athlete &#8211; an individual, who engages in, is eligible to engage in,r may be eligible in the future to engage in, any intercollegiate sport. If anndividual is permanently ineligible to participate in a particularntercollegiate sport, the individual is not a student-athlete for purposes ofhat sport. Void &#8211; of no legal force or effect. Voidable &#8211; capable of being adjudged as having no legal force or effect.
